    {
      "id": "c0e95c18_db582124",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdpx/main/parameters/XacmlPdpParameterHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 60,
      "message": "Oh, just change it to (i.e., leave off the \",e\"):\n\n  LOGGER.error(\"{}\", errorMessage);\n\nSince \"e\" is already passed in the re-thrown exception, sonar doesn't want you to log it here, figuring it will be logged by whatever catches the re-thrown exception.\n\nHowever, simply removing the LOGGER line as you did, works too, since the message will likely by logged by the catcher anyway.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-09-13 18:38:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a2628f28_d44a4dd7",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
